REPORT  ycl_arithmetic_08. "start of report default line with file name.

*declaration of variable var_1 & var_2
*Parameters key used for taking inputs from user
*type is used for defining type of variable int, char, float etc.
*parameters will provide us selection screen

PARAMETERS: var_1 TYPE i,
            var_2 TYPE i.

*data keyword is used for the default variable declaration

DATA: var_3 TYPE i,
      var_4 TYPE i,
      var_5 TYPE i,
      var_6 TYPE i.

var_3 = var_1 + var_2. "command for addition of two numbers
var_4 = var_1 - var_2. "command for subtraction of two numbers
var_5 = var_1 * var_2. "command for multiplication of two numbers
var_6 = var_1 / var_2. "command for division of two numbers

*ULINE AT 1(45) : this command is used for underline (horizontal lines)
*where 1 is cloumn number and 45 is length of line
*sy-vline is used for vertical line
*7 color in abap editor from 1 to 7 keyword is color
*color 1 = Gray-blue
*color 2 = Light gray
*color 3 = Yellow
*color 4 = Blue-green
*color 5 = green
*color 6 = red
*color 7 = orange

ULINE AT 1(45).
WRITE: / sy-vline, 'Result for Addition :', 32 sy-vline, var_3 COLOR 4, 45 sy-vline.
ULINE AT /1(45).

WRITE: / sy-vline, 'Result for Subtraction :', 32 sy-vline, var_4 COLOR 5, 45 sy-vline.
ULINE AT /1(45).

WRITE: / sy-vline, 'Result for Multiplication :', 32 sy-vline, var_5 COLOR 6, 45 sy-vline.
ULINE AT /1(45).

WRITE: / sy-vline, 'Result for Division :', 32 sy-vline, var_6 COLOR 7, 45 sy-vline.
ULINE AT /1(45).
